This paper discusses the problem of mitigating correlation attacks in the Tor network, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves an autonomous system monitor, which is a system-level tool that can be used to monitor and analyze network traffic, making it relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses privacy concerns and preserving user privacy, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (cs.CY).
